        "id": "fb35e1b8"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Service Model Definitions\n",
        "\n",
        "For reference, here are the meanings of the acronyms used in the `service_model` column:\n",
        "\n",
        "*   **CC**: Child Care (General services for children below 7 years old)\n",
        "*   **KN**: Kindergarten (Educational programmes for children aged 4 to 6)\n",
        "*   **DS**: Early Intervention Programme for Infants & Children (EIPIC) Centre / Development Support\n",
        "*   **EYC**: Early Years Centre (Focuses on children aged 2 months to 4 years)\n",
        "*   **EYC-DS**: Early Years Centre with Development Support"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "aef2c3fd"
      },
      "source": [
        "### 3. Vacancy Trends\n",
        "We'll plot the average availability (where 1 means 'Available' and 0 means 'Full') for different levels over the next 7 months to identify which age groups are most constrained."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 361
        },
        "id": "96349a30",
        "outputId": "d76ede19-6d9c-4e3e-b9db-575d378bb448"
      },
      "source": [
        "levels = ['infant', 'pg', 'n1', 'n2', 'k1', 'k2']\n",
        "months = ['current_month', 'next_month', 'third_month', 'fourth_month', 'fifth_month', 'sixth_month', 'seventh_month']\n",
        "\n",
        "vacancy_trends = {}\n",
        "for lvl in levels:\n",
        "    cols = [f'{lvl}_vacancy_{m}' for m in months]\n",
        "    vacancy_trends[lvl] = df[cols].mean().values\n",
        "\n",
        "trends_df = pd.DataFrame(vacancy_trends, index=months)\n",
        "\n",
        "trends_df.plot(figsize=(12, 6), marker='o')\n",
        "plt.title('Average Availability (1=Available, 0=Full) over 7 Months')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Average Availability Score')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Month Index')\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
